# Enum Standards for WindSurf

## Rule: Enum Naming Convention
- All enum files MUST end with `Enum.php`
- The class name MUST match the filename (without `.php`)
- Example: `AppointmentTypeEnum.php` contains `enum AppointmentTypeEnum`

## Rule: Enum Implementation
- All enums MUST implement `Filament\Support\Contracts\HasLabel`
- Use translation keys for all labels
- Include backward compatibility alias

## Rule: Enum Usage
- Always use the full enum class name (with `Enum` suffix) in new code
- The alias (without `Enum`) is only for backward compatibility

## Auto-fix
When creating or renaming enums, automatically:
1. Add `Enum` suffix to the class name if missing
2. Rename the file to match the class name
3. Add backward compatibility alias
4. Update all references in the codebase
